BISHOP SK says his music heals and creates the nature of God in people. Bishop SK, real name Pholoso Seakamela, said he became a professional musician in 2019 after starting off singing at church as a child. He’s also the founder of Heaven on Earth International Ministries in Mahikeng, North West and has a branch in Tembisa, Ekurhuleni. “My aim as a pastor is to minister Christ through music. Preaching and singing are both my callings. “I treat them equally as they accomplish the same purpose,” he said. SK said he sings and preaches around Mzansi. He said he also supports environmental awareness, and has been campaigning in the North West since 2017. “The importance of the environment campaign is to create jobs to the community. We clean parks, schools and teach people about the right to a clean environment.” ALSO READ | DINEO SCORES BIG GIG He released his debut album Reabalocha in 2019, as well as two singles Halempotsa in 2019 and Modimo in 2020. He said he’ll be releasing his second album, A Live Recording, late this year. “Both of my callings make me feel fulfilled as it compliments my legal profession. I’m a qualified lawyer with an LLB degree from University of North West.” Sk, who is busy with his LLM in banking law and also runs a legal consultancy, has shared stages with artists like David Sejake, Peter Mabula and Lucas Maloma.